## Form Design Best Practices

### Layout:
- **One column layouts** are easier to scan than multi-column
- **Group related fields** together with clear section labels
- **Logical order** ‚Äì Follow natural sequence (name, email, phone, address)
- **Show only necessary fields** ‚Äì Every additional field reduces completion rates

### Labels & Instructions:
- **Labels above fields** (not placeholder text as labels)
- **Keep labels short** ‚Äì "Email" not "Please enter your email address"
- **Use helper text** for complex requirements (shown below the field)
- **Mark required fields** clearly ‚Äì Use asterisk (*) or "(required)"

### Validation:
- **Validate on blur** ‚Äì Check fields when user moves away, not on every keystroke
- **Show success states** ‚Äì Green checkmark for valid fields
- **Preserve user input** on errors ‚Äì Don't clear the form
- **Scroll to first error** on form submission

### Smart Defaults:
- **Pre-fill when possible** ‚Äì Use known information (user's name, timezone)
- **Select sensible defaults** ‚Äì Most common option should be pre-selected
- **Remember recent choices** ‚Äì Especially for repeat workflows

### Checkbox & Toggle Semantics

**Checking a checkbox should ENABLE or ADD something, not disable it.** Negative framing increases cognitive load.

#### The Rule:
- ‚úÖ **Checked = ON / Enabled / Active / Included**
- ‚ùå **Checked = OFF / Disabled / Excluded** (avoid this!)

#### Examples:

| ‚ùå Bad (Negative Framing) | ‚úÖ Good (Positive Framing) |
|---------------------------|----------------------------|
| ‚òëÔ∏è "Disable notifications" | ‚òëÔ∏è "Enable notifications" |
| ‚òëÔ∏è "Hide advanced options" | ‚òëÔ∏è "Show advanced options" |
| ‚òëÔ∏è "Don't send me emails" | ‚òëÔ∏è "Send me email updates" |
| ‚òëÔ∏è "Exclude from search" | ‚òëÔ∏è "Include in search" |
| ‚òëÔ∏è "Opt out of tracking" | ‚òëÔ∏è "Allow usage analytics" |

#### Why This Matters:
- Users expect **checked = active/on** (mental model from light switches, etc.)
- Double negatives are confusing: "Uncheck to not disable" = ???
- Scanning a list of checkboxes should quickly show what's enabled

#### Checkbox vs. Toggle:
| Control | Best For |
|---------|----------|
| **Checkbox** | Multiple selections, opt-ins, settings that apply on form submit |
| **Toggle switch** | Binary on/off that takes effect immediately, single settings |

#### Toggle Labels:
- Put the label **before** the toggle, describing what it controls
- The toggle itself shows the state (on/off) ‚Äî don't duplicate in the label
- **Good:** "Email notifications" [toggle]
- **Bad:** "Enable email notifications" [toggle] (redundant with on/off state)

